HEADWORD: Chersonese
<hw>Cher"so*nese</hw> <pr>(k⟦etil⟧r"s⟦osl⟧*n⟦emac⟧s)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[Gr. <grk>cherso`nhsos</grk>; <grk>che`rsos</grk> land +
<grk>nh`sos</grk> island.]</ety> <def>A peninsula; a tract of land
nearly surrounded by water, but united to a larger tract by a neck of
land or isthmus; <as>as, the <ex>Cimbric Chersonese</ex>, or Jutland;
the <ex>Tauric Chersonese</ex>, or Crimea</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Chert</ent>⟦br⟧
